# SOC Lab Overview

**Author:** Bryce Falker  
**Last Updated:** 2026-03-28  
**Lab Type:** IT Help Desk
**Environment:** Virtualized Lab (VirtualBox)

---

## 🎯 Purpose of This Lab

This lab is intended to emulate real-world troubleshooting and common IT problems:
- Software and Application bugs
- Account and Access Issues
- Hardware Issues
- Network and Connectivity problems
- User errors 
- Simple security issues

The purpose is to build hands-on experience addressing everyday IT issues within a simulated enterprise environment.

---

## 🏗️ Lab Architecture

**Components:**
- Windows 10 Client
- Windows Server

 

**Network Layout:**
- Internal network (isolated)
- NAT or host-only networking

---

## 🧰 Tools Used

- Remote Desktop Protocol (RDP)
- Task Manager 
- Command Line

---

## 🧪 Troubleshooting Scenarios Simulated

### 1. Account Login
- User cannot log in
- User locked out of the system
- New users cannot access shared drives or email
- Access Denied when opening a file

---

### 2. Hardware Malfunction
- Computer is running slow  
- Device doesn't connect to the Internet  
- Can't access the printer
- Monitor doesn't display anything 

---

### 3. Network Misconfiguration
- User cannot access websites but internet is connected  
- VPN isn't working

---

### 4. Down Communications 
- User isn't recieving emails  
- User cannot send emails
- Email signature not present

---

### 5. Application Errors 
- Application won't open or crashes on launch 
- User cannot install software
- Application Unresponsive  

---

### 6. User Mistakes
- User accidentally deletes file  
- User cannot find saved file 
- User Interface changes after update 

---

## 🧠 Resolution Strategy
- Gather information to help in initial assessment
- Troubleshoot the issue at hand
- Document the process
- Escalate the issue further if problems reoccur or resolution isn't made

